summary: This document is email correspondence between an FBI agent and an Assistant United States Attorney regarding the preparation and service of subpoenas to USAA and American Express for financial records related to Ghislaine Maxwell. It demonstrates ongoing investigative activity in the Maxwell case in December 2019.

persons.name: G. Maxwell
persons.context: The subpoenas are being prepared to obtain her financial records from USAA and American Express as part of an investigation.

events.title: Subpoenas Prepared for Maxwell Financial Records
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney sends prepared subpoenas for USAA and American Express records related to Ghislaine Maxwell to an FBI agent for service.

locations: Southern District of New York, 1 St. Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
FBI New York Field Office, 26 Federal Plaza, NY, NY 10278
keyFacts: Investigators were actively seeking Ghislaine Maxwell's financial records from USAA and American Express in December 2019.
The correspondence shows coordination between the FBI and the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York in the Maxwell investigation.
The document indicates ongoing investigative efforts targeting Maxwell's financial activities.
